    <section id="id7053128">
      <title>Periodic trends for the main group elements</title>
      <para id="id7084293">Within the main group (s- and p-block) elements there are some general trends that we can observe. </para>
      <list id="id12136376" list-type="bulleted"><item>The further down a given Group the elements have increased metallic character, i.e., good conductors of both heat and electricity, and exhibit delocalized bonding. </item>
        <item>Moving from left to right across a Period the elements have greater non-metallic character, they are insulators with localized bonding. </item>
        <item>Within the p-block at the boundary between the metallic elements (<link target-id="id5055553"/>, grey elements) and nonmetal elements (<link target-id="id5055553"/>, green elements) there is positioned boron and silicon that are metalloid in character (<link target-id="id5055553"/>, pink elements), i.e., they have low electrical conductivity but it increases with temperature. </item>
      </list>
      <para id="id6648869">As an example of these changes <link target-id="id6648875"/> shows the trends across one Period. </para>
